	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Wheeling</placeName> <date>March 21. 1854</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I have recd. your letter<lb/> of bill for the Occident. <sic>Inclosed</sic> you will find<lb/> Six dolls.&#36;6.  <persName>Mr Bloch</persName> &#38; <persName>Mr Heyman</persName>&#44; have requested<lb/> me&#44; to inform you&#44; that they will soon be<lb/> in <placeName>Philaa.</placeName> as they prefer to see the bible<lb/> before selecting one.  I will send my order with<lb/> one of these gentlemen&#44; or probably call on you<lb/> personally.  I have added one subscriber<lb/> for the Occident&#44; address. <persName>Mr. M. Moss</persName>.<lb/> of this place&#44; send him the <date>March</date> number.<lb/>  I will cheerfully continue my exertions&#44; to get subscribers&#44; for your invaluable publication&#44;<lb/> we have an <sic>organised</sic> congregation here&#44;<lb/> numbering from 25 to 30 members&#44; &#38; have also a<lb/> Synagogue there are residing here 17 Jewish<lb/> families&#44; The names of the officers of the Congregation&#44;<lb/> are. <persName>Julius Ballenburg</persName> President&#44; <persName>Mr. M. Moss</persName><lb/> Secretary&#44; Treasurer <persName>Adolph Ballenburg</persName>&#44; the<lb/> congregation have just elected <persName>Mr Joel<lb/> Eppinger</persName>&#44; of <placeName>Bechhofen&#44; Bavaria</placeName>&#44; &#38; lately of<lb/> <placeName>Cincinnati&#44; Ohio</placeName>&#44; to act as Shochet&#44; Hazan&#44;<lb/> &#38; Teacher.</p>
				<p>Very Respectfully your friend &#38; subscriber.</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Daniel Stein</persName></p>
		</body>
